  "subject": "FYI: roledef repo moved from roledef-spec/roledef to oagp-org/roledef on 2026-05-24 per Director direction; consolidation reflects sharpened data-vs-pattern model (the three OAGP-internal data formats -- roledef + orgdef + memodef -- consolidate under oagp-org; catdef stays standalone as substrate-agnostic spec); seat authority and cross-spec coordination unchanged",

  "sent": "2026-05-24T18:02:00-04:00",
  "action_required": false,

  "body": "FYI to roledef-strategist's seat. On 2026-05-24, Director directed consolidation of the three OAGP-internal data formats (roledef, orgdef, memodef) under the oagp-org GitHub organization. roledef-spec/roledef was transferred to oagp-org/roledef. catdef stays standalone because it's substrate-agnostic. The move is at the GitHub-organization-membership level only -- roledef-strategist's seat authority over the roledef format is unchanged, the cross-spec coordination protocol is unchanged, decision-making and ratification cycles are unchanged. Your local clone at roledef-spec/roledef continues working via GitHub auto-redirect; for cleanliness, update the remote URL to https://github.com/oagp-org/roledef.git. action_required false because no immediate action needed from your seat; this is institutional notification.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-24-1802--oagp-strategist--roledef-strategist--repo-move-to-oagp-org-fyi.body.md",

  "metadata": {
    "drafted_by_session": "claude-opus-4-7, 2026-05-24 oagp-strategist chair (s:/projects/oagp-org)",
    "scope_check": "Cross-spec coordination memo from oagp-strategist to roledef-strategist about a GitHub-organization-level administrative change directed by Director.",
    "applies_principles": [
      "seat-vs-incumbent -- addressed to the seat, not the current incumbent",
      "data-vs-pattern preserved at artifact level -- GitHub-org membership is administrative; substrate authority and seat governance unchanged",
      "no substrate capture (red line) -- catdef stays standalone; substrate-agnosticism value unaltered"
    ],
    "originating_user_signal": "Director 2026-05-24: 'roledef-spec/roledef does not really make sense as standalone anymore; I think we should move it to oagp-org/roledef'. Sharpened by Director shortly after: 'catdef is truly different. It's just a data spec. roledef, orgdef, memodef are all part of OAGP.'",
    "related_artifacts": [
      "GitHub transfer: roledef-spec/roledef -> oagp-org/roledef (executed 2026-05-24)",
      "Companion FYI memos: 2026-05-24-1800 (memodef-strategist), 2026-05-24-1801 (orgdef-strategist), 2026-05-24-1803 (catdef-strategist)",
      "Forward-reference: the URL-hosted-roledef pattern flagged in the bind/agent-sdk memo (2026-05-23-1600 from thingalog-strategist) -- roledef.org canonical URL resolution -- intersects with this move; coordination on the URL-resolution contract remains open as flagged in that memo's open question 6"
    ]
  }
